content: Great game! Pay once and no pay for play or ads, just as it should be.. Simple rules, good difficulty curve... I am picky and I like this game! :c)
5 stars for the zero permission requirements, but it needs some updates for adding features such as hints and smoother ooerating on newer android versions. Overall a great arcade puzzle game.

Got this because it was free. I thought it was going to be total pants if it they were giving it away. I was so wrong. It is a smile inducing delight, it is as charming as it is frustrating and I am hooked. Well done you lot. 12th Sept 2020 This has lived on all my phones and gets replayed more than console games. It's a classic. No Gorb 2, it's a crime. But hey! That's a compliment. Whatever you're doing good luck. And thanks. Probably chilled me more than a couple of shots of Jack.

GORB is great fun! I love how the challenge level ramps up as you play, and everything is very clearly laid out, with tutorial levels built in as you go. This takes simple premise, designed very well to make a tricky brain teaser. Works flawlessly on my Samsung Galaxy Note 3 (yeah it used to be flagship but it's old now!). Goofy design, sounds and music fit the theme perfectly. This game is genuinely a lot of fun. I've not finished it yet (about half way through so far), but I've seen enough to say to anyone reading this who hasn't got GORB yet: Get it. It's great! Oh, and a BIG plus in my book is the no ads (yeah it's paid but c'mon it's cheap for what you get), no IAP, no permissions nonsense that plagues the sector at the minute.
It's really fun and it does involve a lot of thinking that's what I love some of the levels are hard but that only makes it better my baby brother lives this game and asks me for help a lot

Great game! Gorb (Green, Orange, Red, Blue) is a unique game. Buy it as 
soon as you can. I spent countless of hours until I finished all worlds 
with maximum stars and boy! The bonus level is definitely worth it! 
Sometimes I couldn't sleep until I found the right moves :). I passed a lot 
of levels with less moves than suggested. Any future plans to reward the 
most dedicated players?

Game play is fun. The messages printed after a level are starting to get on 
my nerves. I'm on world three, so a good way in, but not nearly completed. 
Not sure I want to see "That was embarrassing" or the like ever again 
though.

The instructions are part of the game.  It has a built-in tutorial.  There is also an official walk-through posted, but you should only use it when you are truly stuck.  See here:

content: Lovely little physics-based puzzle game, with simple yet deceptively deep gameplay. Can be frustrating when you're juuuust short of a perfect run, but the balance is such that you always want to try again. No ads, in-app purchase or required permissions -- fantastic! I picked this up free on sale, but would happily have paid the small regular asking price. The game didn't nag me to rate five stars like too many others do, but I'm choosing to do so because I think it's great.
